# Hermes migration / server rebuild template
#
# This is a small, migration-focused template for rebuilding this Hermes setup.
# For the full upstream environment catalog, see:
#   .env.example
#
# Recommended workflow:
#   1. Copy this file to ~/.hermes/.env on the new server
#   2. Fill in only the real secrets you need
#   3. Keep the real filled-in file out of git

# =============================================================================
# MODEL / PROVIDER NOTES
# =============================================================================
# OpenAI Codex OAuth is not configured here; restore it with Hermes auth/login
# if you depend on it.
#
# OpenRouter/Gemini are included here because they are standard Hermes env vars
# documented in .env.example and are common fallback/provider choices.

OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_API_KEY=
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# WEB / RESEARCH TOOLS
# =============================================================================
# Firecrawl is currently used in this setup.
FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=

# Add any additional non-upstream/custom integration secrets below if your
# deployment depends on them. Keep names consistent with the code/config that
# reads them.
#
# Example placeholders for local operational use:
# CUSTOM_API_KEY=
# ANOTHER_SERVICE_TOKEN=

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - Many Hermes settings live in ~/.hermes/config.yaml, not here.
# - Messaging platform setup may also depend on config.yaml and Hermes gateway
#   setup flows, not only environment variables.
# - If you restore from a full `hermes backup`, that backup may also restore
#   the existing ~/.hermes/.env file. This template is mainly for clean rebuilds
#   and secret re-entry.
